Pre-Arrival Preparation:
- Confirm start date and employee details from HR
- Verify manager and department information
- Determine required equipment and access based on role
- Schedule onboarding tasks to complete before start date

Hardware Provisioning:
- Allocate laptop/desktop from inventory
- Image device with standard corporate build
- Install role-specific software
- Configure device name and asset tag
- Prepare peripherals (monitor, keyboard, mouse, headset)
- Set up docking station if required

Account Creation:
- Create Active Directory / Azure AD account
- Set up email mailbox and configure aliases
- Assign appropriate Microsoft 365 / Google Workspace license
- Configure email signature template
- Add to department distribution lists

Access Provisioning:
- Add user to department security groups
- Provision access to shared drives and folders
- Configure VPN access if remote work enabled
- Set up access to required business applications
- Create accounts in department-specific systems

{% if role_type == 'remote' %}
Remote Worker Setup:
- Ship equipment to user's home address
- Include VPN setup instructions
- Configure softphone or Teams calling
- Ensure remote access tools are installed
{% endif %}

Communication Setup:
- Add user to Teams/Slack channels
- Configure voicemail if applicable
- Set up any required integrations

Documentation Package:
- Prepare welcome email with login instructions
- Include IT policies and acceptable use information
- Provide self-service portal information
- Document emergency IT contact information

Day-One Support:
- Verify user can log in successfully
- Confirm email access is working
- Test access to required applications
- Schedule IT orientation if available
- Provide help desk contact information

Completion:
- Update asset management records
- Notify manager of IT readiness
- Document all provisioned access and equipment
- Close onboarding ticket
